# HoloCollabEduMeet Technology Stack

Based on my audit of your project architecture, dependencies, and routing mechanisms, here is the comprehensive list of the modern technology stack utilized in this application.

## Frontend (Client Application)
- **Framework**: React 19 (via Vite 7 build tool)
- **Language**: TypeScript (v5.9)
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS 4 with PostCSS architecture
- **Icons & UI Utilities**: `lucide-react`, `clsx`, `tailwind-merge`
- **Animation**: Framer Motion
- **Routing**: React Router DOM (v7)
- **3D Graphics & AR**: Three.js (v0.182.0)
- **Computer Vision (Frontend Inference)**: MediaPipe (`@mediapipe/camera_utils`, `@mediapipe/hands`)
- **Real-Time Communication**: Socket.io Client (v4.8)

## Backend (API & Real-Time Services)
- **Framework**: FastAPI (v0.104.1) serving via Uvicorn asynchronous workers.
- **Language**: Python 3
- **Microservices Architecture**: The backend is fractured into independent modular services (Core API, AI Service, CV Service, Realtime Service) running on separate ports.
- **Database ORM**: SQLAlchemy 2.0 (with `asyncpg` for non-blocking operations)
- **Database Engine**: PostgreSQL
- **Data Validation & Parsing**: Pydantic v2
- **Authentication**: JWT (JSON Web Tokens) via `python-jose` with native `bcrypt` password hashing.
- **WebSocket Protocol Engines**: `python-socketio` and FastAPI's native `WebSocket` classes.
- **Microservice Networking**: `httpx` for internal asynchronous inter-service HTTP requests.

## Cloud & AI Integrations 
- **Generative Models**: Prepared for dynamic routing to OpenAI (`gpt-4`), Google (`gemini-pro`), and DeepSeek (`deepseek-chat`).

The integration between these layers relies heavily on **WebSocket Authoritative State Syncing**, allowing standard REST APIs (FastAPI) to manage persistence while Socket/WS modules broadcast high-fidelity 3D transformation matrices (Three.js coordinates) concurrently.
